# PKM Box Store Project Rules

## Project Overview
PKM Box Store is a Pokemon card box shopping mall project.

## Stack
- Backend: Spring Boot, MySQL, JWT, Toss Payments, AWS S3
- Frontend: Next.js App Router, TypeScript, CSS in globals.css
- Do not introduce Tailwind CSS or external UI libraries unless explicitly requested.

## General Rules
- Do not change backend code when the task is frontend-only.
- Do not change frontend code when the task is backend-only.
- Preserve existing API calls, routing, authentication, and state management unless the task explicitly asks to change them.
- Do not add mock data to replace real API data.
- Always check existing files before editing.
- After frontend changes, run `npm run build` from `frontend`.
- After backend changes, run `.\gradlew.bat test --no-daemon` from `backend`.

## Frontend Rules
- Use existing `frontend/lib/api.ts`.
- Use existing `frontend/types/api.ts`.
- Use existing `RequireAuth`.
- Prefer editing `frontend/app/globals.css` for styling.
- Keep mobile responsiveness.
- Do not remove existing user flows:
  - product list
  - product detail
  - cart
  - direct purchase
  - order/payment
  - admin pages

## Backend Rules
- Follow existing domain package structure.
- Use existing BusinessException and ErrorCode.
- Keep existing security rules.
- Do not commit real secrets.